### HYMN CXIV

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_2011401">1</span></span>O Indra,
from all ancient time rivalless ever and companionless  
   art thou:  
  In war thou seekest comradeship.  
<span class="margnote"><span id="an_2011402">2</span></span>Thou findest
not the wealthy man to be thy friend: those scorn  
   thee who are flown with wine.  
  What time thou thunderest and gatherest, then thou, even as a  
   father, art invoked.

